body:
Mama Danvers

Request: “Maybe a carol danvers x daughter reader. Reader is around 5/6 years old and is carol’s biological daughter, and has a little bit of her powers. Carol takes her to meet all of the avengers. She is very shy when meeting them and they are shocked that carol is an actual momma. Just a cute fluffy fic. The snap also never happened ❤ thank you if you can. ”

A/N: We’re gonna say that because the Snap didn’t happen, Tony and Pepper just had Morgan, so she’s a baby while reader is six. Also, sorry it’s short! I can write more parts to it later if you guys want

Carol had a hectic life. She was basically the Avengers for planets all over the universe, she had regular check-ins with the Avengers on Earth, and she had Y/N to take care of. That little girl meant the world to her and more, but it wasn’t very easy to be there for her all the time. A few weeks after Y/N’s sixth birthday, Carol decided to take a trip to Earth. Y/N had been asking to visit Uncle Fury and Goose for months, so she brought her along.

Steve Rogers was waiting for Carol just outside the compound. She had told him she’d be coming and that she wouldn’t be alone. He had figured she was bringing a friend, so one could imagine his surprise when Carol approached him with a small child wrapped in her arms. Before he could ask about the child, Carol walked past and went into the compound.

Y/N wiggled out of her mom’s arms when she saw Fury, rushing over to him and holding up her arms. He gently picked her up as Carol came to meet him. They both greeted each other kindly as they headed towards the living room in the compound where the rest of the Avengers were gathered.

Peter was the first to notice the quiet little girl balanced on Fury’s shoulders. He gave her a bright smile, which she shyly returned before expertly climbing from Fury’s shoulders to her mother’s. Carol had some explaining to do while Y/N sat on the couch beside her and played with the Flerken. Peter brought Morgan over to Y/N, hoping that the baby would help put the little girl at ease enough to talk to him.

“Hi, Y/N! This is Morgan. Do you want to say hello?” The teen sat in front of the couch, his mentor’s baby girl sitting in his lap.

Y/N glanced to her mom first, who nodded softly at her as she kept talking, before moving to the edge of the couch cushion to quietly talk to Morgan. “Hi, Morgan. How old are you?”

Peter waved the baby’s hands a bit as he answered in a slightly falsetto voice. “I’m six months old! How old are you?”

“I’m six!” Y/N giggled a bit at Peter’s antics, smiling and beginning to talk with him.

Carol was trying to listen to what Rhodey and Steve were talking about, but she kept looking at her daughter, distracted by the joy and laughter coming from the toddler. It took her a few minutes to realize that Tony and Pepper were doing the same thing, starting at their baby and the boy they practically considered a son. The three laughing children would be close, Carol could tell. Y/N would be begging her to visit Earth more often, too. But as long as her daughter was happy, Carol could handle that.

summary: Someone write a ‘Capitan Marvel Goes to Sephora’ fanfic please
title: Someone write a ‘Capitan Marvel Goes to Sephora’ fanfic please
body:
I want a fic where Carol Danvers. Airforce pilot and Defender of the Universe. 

Winds up stuck in a makeup chair at Sephora getting her face poked by some civilian with a handful of brushes. 

And she’s confused, uncomfortable, hasn’t worn makeup in a decade and isn’t sure how she feels about it. And Does Not Think About how it does look rather glamorous. Maybe is kinda annoyed at everyone telling her how much ‘better’ she looks now, or how ‘beautiful you are with makeup’ and she just wants to be like “Well Fuck y’all”. 

And then her leaving for whatever plot contrivance that needed her to get makeup in the first place. 

And her in front of a mirror and sink, considering washing it off before meeting the Avengers. And going ‘nah’. 

(Which turns out to be a good thing. It turns out this new 2019 makeup is ‘last all day’ and ‘waterproof’ and trying to scrub it off that night with warm water and hand soap just makes her look like a raccoon.

And then everyone being like ‘you look tired’ or ‘you look goth’ the next day

And then she swears off makeup forever; the end.
